org.snrg_nyc.ui

Interface UI_Interface


  • public interface UI_Interface
    The public-facing business logic for use by the user interface of an SNRG frontend. This should be called by the UI code instead of any internal classes.
    Version:
    0.1
    Author:
    Devin Hastings

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  UI_Interface.UIException
      An internal class that is the root of all UI exceptions.

        Get the time at which a file was last modified in identical format to File.lastModified().

      • scratch_updateRangeMin

        boolean scratch_updateRangeMin(int id,
                               int min)
                        throws UI_Interface.UIException
        Add/Update the lower bound of an Integer Range property.
        Parameters:
        id - The ID from scratch_addRange()
        min - The new lower bound. It cannot overlap with another range, and must be smaller than the upper bound
        Returns:
        The success of the change (if false, the lower bound was not changed). The most likely cause of a failed change is that the requirements for the value were not met.
        Throws:
        UI_Interface.UIException - Thrown if the id does not point to a range item.

        Returns:
        The success of the change (if false, the lower bound was not changed). The most likely cause of a failed change is that the requirements for the value were not met.
        Throws:

                                                 throws UI_Interface.UIException
        Get all of the range labels for the scratch property

      • scratch_addConditionalDistribution

        int scratch_addConditionalDistribution(java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.String> dependencyConditions,
                                       java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Float> probabilities)
                                throws UI_Interface.UIException
        Add a conditional Distribution to the current scratch property
        Parameters:
        dependencyConditions - A map of integer IDs, which must be one of the IDs from scratch_getDependencies()(); and labels that the dependency must be, which is one of nodeProp_getRangeLabels(int)(pid). All pIDs are optional, but there must be exactly one label per pID.
        probabilities - A map of the scratch property's range labels, as received from scratch_getRangeLabels(), to floating-point probabilities (these probabilities are relative, and there is no special requirements for them). Each label must be in the map exactly once.
        Returns:
        The ID of the new conditional Distribution
        Throws:
        UI_Interface.UIException - Thrown if the dependencyConditions or probabilities aren't valid.

      • scratch_removeConditionalDistribution

        void scratch_removeConditionalDistribution(int id)
                                    throws UI_Interface.UIException
        This removes a conditional distribution from the scratch property.
        Parameters:
        id - The ID of the conditional distribution, as received from scratch_addConditionalDistribution(Map, Map) or scratch_getConditionalDistributionIDs()
        Throws:
        UI_Interface.UIException - Thrown if the ID does not exist.

      • scratch_updateConditionalDistribution

        void scratch_updateConditionalDistribution(int id,
                                           java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.String> dependencyConditions,
                                           java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Float> probabilities)
                                    throws UI_Interface.UIException
        Replace the attributes of a conditional distribution with new information.

        See scratch_addConditionalDistribution(java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer, java.lang.String>, java.util.Map<java.lang.String, java.lang.Float>) for the requirements of dependencyConditions and probabilities.

        Parameters:
        id - The ID of the conditional distribution, as received from scratch_addConditionalDistribution(Map, Map) or scratch_getConditionalDistributionIDs()
        dependencyConditions - See scratch_addConditionalDistribution(java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer, java.lang.String>, java.util.Map<java.lang.String, java.lang.Float>) for requirements
        probabilities - See scratch_addConditionalDistribution(java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer, java.lang.String>, java.util.Map<java.lang.String, java.lang.Float>) for requirements
        Throws:
        UI_Interface.UIException - Thrown if the ID does not point to a distribution, or the requirements for the parameters are not met.

      • scratch_reorderConditionalDistributions

        void scratch_reorderConditionalDistributions(java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> ordering)
                                      throws UI_Interface.UIException
        Set the order in which the conditional distributions are to be checked.
        Parameters:
        ordering - A list of IDs of the conditional distributions in the order they are to be checked
        Throws:
        UI_Interface.UIException - Thrown if any of the IDs in the list do not point to a conditional distribution in the scratch object.

      • scratch_setDefaultDistribution

        void scratch_setDefaultDistribution(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Float> distribution)
                             throws UI_Interface.UIException
        Set the default distribution of the scratch property.
        Parameters:
        distribution - A map of range labels from scratch_getRangeLabels() and floating point values representing the probability of that range in the distribution. Each label must appear exactly once in the map.
        Throws:
        UI_Interface.UIException - Thrown if the requirements for the distribution are not met.

      • scratch_getDefaultDistribution

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Float> scratch_getDefaultDistribution()
        Return the default distribution as a map, similar to scratch_getDistribution(int) .
        Returns:
        A map of the range labels in the scratch property to their probabilities in the distribution.
